owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: covalently_bonded_to
owl:ObjectProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: y is covalently_bonded_to z iff [(y and z are atoms) and (there exists a covalent bond between y and z)]

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: covalently_connected_to
owl:ObjectProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: m Covalently_connected_to n iff (m and n are part of molecules) and there exist x and y such that (x and y are atoms) and x part_of m and y part_of n and x covalently_bonded_to y.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: weakly_interacting_with
owl:ObjectProperty.obo:IAO_0000115: x weakly_interating_with y iff [(x and y are Instances_of (material entity)) and there is an (not covalent) attractive interaction between x and y which are spatially adjacent.]
Pairwise interaction of the sugar edge with a phosphate unit. Only occurs with G.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base pair consists of a pair of nucleotide residues that interact by nucleoside edge to nucleoside edge hydrogen bonds.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: deoxyribose ring
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A ribose ring that does not have a hydroxy group at the 2' position.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_1_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_1_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which the two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Watson-Crick edges of each base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "cis" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_2_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_2_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which the two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Watson-Crick edges of each base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "trans" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_3_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000112: Forbidden pairings (Watson-Crick edge first); CA, UC, AC, AA, GC, GU.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_3_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Watson-Crick edge of one base and the Hoogsteen edge of the other base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "cis" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_4_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000112: Forbidden are the following pairings (Watson-Crick edge first); CU, UC, AC, AU, GC, GA.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_4_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Watson-Crick edge of one base and the Hoogsteen edge of the other base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "trans" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_5_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_5_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Watson-Crick edge of one base and the Sugar edge of the other base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "cis" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_6_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_6_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Watson-Crick edge of one base and the Sugar edge of the other base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "trans" relative to each other.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000112: Forbidden is the pairing where G presents the Watson-Crick edge and A presents the sugar edge.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_7_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_7_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Hoogsteen edges of each base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "cis" relative to each other.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000112: Forbidden pairings are: CC, CU, CA, UA, UC, UG, UU, AC, AU, AA and GU.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_8_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_8_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Hoogsteen edges of each base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "trans" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_9_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_9_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Hoogsteen edge of one base and the Sugar edge of the other base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "cis" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_10_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_10_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Hoogsteen edge of one base and the Sugar edge of the other base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "trans" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_11_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_11_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Sugar edges of each base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "cis" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: family_12_base_pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000112: Excluded are CA, CC, CU, CG, and UA, UC, UU, UG.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A family_12_base_pair is an RNAO_base_pair in which two RNA nucleotides interact by edge-to-edge hydrogen-bonding between the Sugar edges of each base and in which the glycosidic bonds of the two nucleotides are oriented "trans" relative to each other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: canonical RNA base pair
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An RNAO_base_pair which has cis-Watson--Crick pairing and where the participating bases are AU, CG, GC or UA.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleobase
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A nucleobase is an N-heterocyclic group that forms part of a nucleoside residue.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: phosphate moiety
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A phosphate group consists of a phosphorus atom doubly-bonded to two oxygen atoms and singly-bonded to two oxygen atoms, both of which have a free valence. Unlike the phosphate group in ChEBI (CHEBI:32958), the RNAO phosphate group has two free valences.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribonucleoside residue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A ribonucleoside consists of a nitrogen heterocycle (a nucleobase) covalently bonded to a ribose ring, with free valences at the 3' and 5' positions on the ring.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribonucleotide residue
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A ribonucleotide consists of a nitrogen heterocyclic group covalently bonded to the 4' position of a ribose ring and a phosphate group covalently bonded the 3' position of the ribose ring. There is a free valence on one of the oxygens of the phosphate group and on the 5' position of the ribose ring.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: ribose ring
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A ribose ring is a furanose ring with free valences at the 4' position (to bond to the nucleobase), and the 3' and 5' positions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: purine nucleobase
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A purine nucleobase is a heterocyclic group consisting of a five-membered aromatic ring ortho,para-fused to a six-membered aromatic ring and where the atoms at the 1-, 3-, 7- and 9- positions are nitrogen atoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: pyrimidine nucleobase
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A pyrimidine nucleobase is a heterocyclic group consisting of a six-membered ring where the atoms at the 1- and 3-positions are nitrogen atoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: cytosine nucleobase
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A cytosine nucleobase is a pyrimidine that contains a 4-amino group and a 2-oxo group and has a free valence at the 1-position.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: uracil nucleobase
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A uracil nucleobase is a pyrimidine nucleobase that contains a 2-oxo group and a 4-oxo group and has a free valence at the 1-position.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: adenine nucleobase
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An adenine nucleobase is a purine nucleobase that contains a 6-amino group and a free valence at the 9-position.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: guanine nucleobase
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A guanine nucleobase is a purine nucleobase that contains a 2-amino group, a 6-oxo group and a free valence at the 9-position.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleoside edge
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A nucleoside edge is either a Watson-Crick edge or a Hoogsteen edge or a sugar edge.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Watson-Crick edge
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The Watson-Crick edge of a nucleobase is the preferred edge along which it undergoes hydrogen bonding with other nucleobases.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Hoogsteen edge
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The Hoogsteen edge of a nucleobase is the edge of the nucleobase which is not adjacent to the 2'-hydroxyl group on the ribose ring.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: sugar edge
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The sugar edge of a nucleoside consists of the edge of the nucleobase adjacent ot the 2'-hydroxyl group on the ribose ring and the 2'-hydroxyl group on the ribose ring.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: paired region
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of one or more adjacent nucleotide residues in which at least one residue is part of a base pair.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: unpaired region
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of one or more nucleotides that are not involved in base pairing.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: unbroken stem
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A paired region made up of two contiguous collections of nucleotides, in which each nucleotide forms a base pair.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: terminal loop
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A contiguous sequence of nucleotide residues that directly links the two halves of an unbroken stem (but does not participate in the stem); this structure is also known as a "hairpin loop". Because a terminal loop may also participate in other inter-base interactions, (a) it is defined relative to a particular unbroken_stem, and (b) it is not implicitly defined as unpaired (or paired).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: internal loop
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of nucleotide residues that link two given unbroken_stems.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: this term encompasses the concepts of "bulge" and "mismatch" as well. Again, this term is defined relative to two particular unbroken_stems and does not imply unpairedness (or pairedness).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: stem junction
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of nucleotide residues consisting of all and only the nucleotide regions that link more than two unbroken stems such that each region links exactly two unbroken stems. This term is defined relative to the particular unbroken_stems involved and, again, does not imply anything about the pairedness/unpairedness of the bases in this region. The degree of a junction is a property (e.g. 3-junction, 4-junction), so the different degrees do not get separate entries in the ontology.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: strand end
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A sequence_region bounded at one end by the 5' or 3' end of the molecule, and at the other by an unbroken_stem.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: collection of nucleotides residues
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A collection of nucleotide residues is a part of a nucleic acid consisting of one or more nucleotides.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: conformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: The spatial arrangement of the atoms in a molecule or molecular part affording distinction between stereoisomers which can be interconverted by rotations about formally single bonds.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base pair orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A conformation that inheres in an RNA base pair. It may be cis- or trans- depending on the orientations of the ribose rings relative to the edge-edge interaction of the nucleobases.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000117: PERSON: Colin Batchelor, based on the Leontis-Westhof classification.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base pair cis-orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base pair conformation where the ribose rings are on the same side of a plane drawn through the middle of the edge-edge hydrogen bonds.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000117: PERSON: Colin Batchelor, based on the Leontis-Westhof classification.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base pair trans-orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base pair conformation where the ribose rings are on opposite sides of a plane drawn through the middle of the edge-edge hydrogen bonds.
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000117: PERSON: Colin Batchelor, based on the Leontis-Westhof classification.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: nucleoside conformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A conformation that inheres in an nucleoside based on the rotation of the nucleobase about the glycosidic torsion angle χ with the furanose.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: syn nucleoside conformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A syn nucleoside conformation is a nucleoside conformation characterized by the nucleobase being oriented towards the ribose due to rotation about the glycosidic torsion angle χ. From χ = 0°, where the plane of the base is aligned with the O4’-C1’ bond in a direction towards the O4’ atom, the syn conformation covers the remaining rotations of ±90°: χ = [-90°, 90°].

owl:Class.rdfs:label: anti nucleoside conformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A anti nucleoside conformation is a nucleoside conformation characterized by the nucleobase being oriented away from the ribose due to rotation about the glycosidic torsion angle χ. From χ = 180°, where the plane of the base is aligned with the O4’-C1’ bond in a direction away from the O4’ atom, the anti conformation covers a rotations of ±90°: χ = [-180°, 90°].

owl:Class.rdfs:label: envelope conformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An envelope conformation is a furan ring conformation in which only one of the five fruan atoms (C1’, C2’, C3’, C4’ or O4’) is out of the plane formed by the four others.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: twist conformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An envelope conformation is a furan ring conformation in which two atoms are in opposite sides of the plane formed by the remaining three.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: furan ring conformation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A furan ring conformation is a conformation that inheres in a furan ring and is characterized by the values of torsion angles: θ0-4.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: C2’-endo pucker
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: C2'-endo pucker (<sup>2</sup>E conformation) is an envelope conformation in which the C2' atom is above the plane formed by the other 4 atoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: C3’-endo pucker
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: C3'-endo pucker (An <sup>3</sup>E conformation) is an envelope conformation in which the C3' atom is above the plane formed by the other 4 atoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: C4’-exo pucker
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: C4'-exo pucker (E<sub>4</sub> conformation) is an envelope conformation in which the C4' atom is below the plane formed by the other 4 atoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: C3'-endo - C4' -exo pucker
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: C3'-endo - C4' exo pucker (<sup>3</sup>E<sub>4</sub> conformation) is a twist conformation in which the C3' atom is above the plane and the C4' atom is below the plane.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: C3'-endo - C2' -exo pucker
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: C3'-endo - C2' exo pucker (<sup>3</sup>E<sub>2</sub> conformation) is a twist conformation in which the C3' atom is above the plane and the C2' atom is below the plane.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack consists of a pair of nucleotides that interact by London dispersion inter-molecular interactions between their nucleobases such that one base is stacked on top of the other.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: adjacent base stack
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An adjacent base stack is a base stack between a pair of sequence-adjacent nucleotides.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: non-adjacent base stack
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A non-adjacent base stack is a base stack between a pair of non sequence-adjacent nucleotides.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack orientation is a conformation that inheres in a base stack by virtue of the orientation of the nucleobases relative to i) the alignment of base normals and ii) their sequence adjacency.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack straight orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An base stack straight orientation is a base stack orientation in which the normals of both bases are aligned in the same direction.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack reverse orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack reverse orientation is a base stack orientation in which the normals of both bases are aligned in the opposite directions.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack base-normal orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack base-normal orientation is a base stack orientation that depends on the relative orientation of the base normals.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack above orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack above orientation is a base stack orientation in which the second base (B) is in the same direction as the normal to the first base (A).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack below orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack below orientation is a base stack orientation in which the normal of the second base (B) is directed towards the first base (A).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack sequence adjacency
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack sequence adjacency is a base stack orientation that depends on whether the stacked nucleobases are part of nucleotides that are sequence adjacent or not.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack adjacent base orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack adjacent orientation is a base stack orientation in which the stacked nucleobases are part of nucleotides that are sequence adjacent.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: base stack non-adjacent base orientation
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A base stack non-adjacent orientation is a base stack orientation in which the stacked nucleobases are part of nucleotides that are not sequence adjacent.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: furanose ring
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A furanose ring is a ring that consists of four carbon and one oxygen atom and has free valences at each carbon position.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: upward base stack
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An upward base stack is a base stack that exhibits both an straight orientation and an above orientation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: downward base stack
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A downward base stack is a base stack that exhibits both an straight orientation and a below orientation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: inward base stack
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An inward base stack is a base stack that exhibits both a reverse orientation and an above orientation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: outward base stack
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An outward base stack is a base stack that exhibits both a reverse orientation and a below orientation.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: submolecule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a submolecule is a part of a molecule that consists of covalently bonded sum of a collection of atoms.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: part of molecule
owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: a part of molecule is some part of a molecule.
